Recommended Books





Recommended Books
We are often asked to recommend books for people interested in learning about investing. Below is a list of some of our favourites.


Book Recommendation: “Fooled by Randomness”
December 7, 2008
A concise and highly insightful book on the crucial role of chance in investing, and in life – and on…  Continue reading
Tags:
Investor Psychology


Book Recommendation: “The Little Book of Value Investing”

This book describes how a highly disciplined investor is virtually certain to beat the market over time if he or…  Continue reading
Tags:
Value Investing


Book Recommendation: “The Little Book of Common Sense Investing”

This book points out that, after fees, less than 10% of active investment managers can beat the relevant stock market…  Continue reading
Tags:
Dividends, Investment Managers, Value Investing


Book Recommendation: “The Little Book of Behavioural Investing”

This book explains why most investors (including the pros) underperform the index — i.e. how, when it comes to investing, human…  Continue reading
Tags:
Investor Psychology, Long-Term Investing


Book Recommendation: “The Intelligent Investor”

The timeless classic on value investing. Read especially the Introduction and Chapters 8 and 20. The Appendix includes Buffett’s famous…  Continue reading
Tags:
Long-Term Investing, Value Investing


Book Recommendation: “The Essays of Warren Buffett, Lessons for Corporate America”

Selected, arranged, and introduced by the publisher, Lawrence A. Cunningham. A well thought out compilation of Warren Buffett’s letters to…  Continue reading
Tags:
Investment Managers, Value Investing











