CLOSE X

Adriana Cano
Partner
Client Services & Operations


Adriana is one of Longview’s Managers of Client Services & Operations. In this role she and Denise are in charge of administering client portfolios and acting as our main contact with our custodian.
An experienced administrator, Adriana previously spent six years as a Team Leader in Unitholder Recordkeeping at CIBC Mellon Global Securities Services, followed by eight years as a Senior Portfolio Administrator at TD Harbour Capital, a division of TD Private Investment Counsel.
Adriana is bilingual (English and Spanish), and is a graduate of York University in Economics and Accounting.
When not helping Longview’s clients, Adriana enjoys spending time with her family and friends, keeping abreast of current events and news, and has a love for soccer.
acano@longviewassets.com














 

CLOSE X

James Eaton, CFA
Partner
Member, Investment Committee
 


As a member of Longview’s Investment Committee, James shares responsibility for the firm’s investment decisions. In addition, along with Alvin and Tom, James is responsible for undertaking primary research on companies in the Longview Portfolio and other potential investments.
Prior to joining Longview, James was an Investment Analyst at Invesco Ltd. where he identified, analyzed and recommended investments for the Toronto-based Trimark team.  Among his covered mandates, the Invesco Canadian Pool was a 1st quartile product over a 5 year period, and the Canadian Enhanced Dividend Pool, for which he shared portfolio management responsibilities, was 1st quartile since its launch in 2012.
James is a CFA® charterholder.  He received an MBA from Schulich School of Business, where he was on the Dean’s Honour List, and a Bachelor of Commerce with Distinction from Dalhousie University.
Away from the office, James enjoys spending time with his family, travel, and recreational sports such as triathlons, skiing and hockey.
jeaton@longviewassets.com
Connect on LinkedIn














 

CLOSE X

Denise Fernandes
Partner
Client Services & Operations


Denise is one of Longview’s Managers of Client Services & Operations.  In this role she and Adriana are in charge of administering client portfolios and acting as Longview’s main contact with our custodian.
Denise has over 26 years in banking and private investment management.  Prior to working at Longview, she was a Senior Portfolio Administrator, at TD Harbour Capital, a division of TD Wealth, Private Investment Counsel.  She also has experience in back office and custodial operations in her roles as a Team Manager and Account Manager at TD Waterhouse Canada Inc., Institutional Services.
Denise graduated from Seneca College in Business Administration and has a post graduate in Human Resources Management.
In her spare time, Denise enjoys spending time with her four children, family and friends.  She also likes to read and do numerical puzzles and crosswords.
dfernandes@longviewassets.com
Connect on LinkedIn














 

CLOSE X

Tom Lace, CFA, CPA, CA
Partner
Member, Investment Committee
 


As a member of Longview’s Investment Committee, Tom shares responsibility for the firm’s investment decisions. In addition, along with Alvin and James, Tom is responsible for undertaking primary research on companies in the Longview Portfolio and other potential investments.
Prior to joining Longview, Tom was a Senior Associate at PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC) in their Audit practice, where he focused on clients in the banking, brokering, insurance and technology sectors.  While at PwC, Tom earned his CPA, CA designation.  He is also a CFA charterholder.
Tom is a graduate of the University of Notre Dame, where he graduated cum laude with a degree in Business Administration, majoring in accounting and sociology.  Tom also graduated with Beta Alpha Psi and Phi Kappa Delta distinctions and a certificate in Asia Pacific Business.
Beyond Longview, Tom is the founder of the Horizons High School program.  In his spare time, Tom enjoys reading, travelling, numerous sports and spending time with family and friends.
tlace@longviewassets.com
Connect on LinkedIn














 

CLOSE X

Alvin Lau, CFA
Partner
Member, Investment Committee


As a member of Longview’s Investment Committee, Alvin shares responsibility for the firm’s investment decisions. In addition, along with James and Tom, Alvin is responsible for undertaking primary research on companies in the Longview Portfolio and other potential investments.
Prior to joining Longview, Alvin was a Manager at CIBC Leveraged Finance where he focused on structuring debt financing for mid-market private equity clients and corporate clients. In this capacity, one of his primary responsibilities was to analyze and value companies across a broad range of industries.
Alvin is a CFA charterholder. He received an Honours Business Administration degree, with Distinction, from the Richard Ivey School of Business at the University of Western Ontario. He is a passionate value investor who makes a practice of attending the Berkshire Hathaway annual shareholder meeting in Omaha.
When not researching investment ideas, Alvin enjoys spending time with his wife and young son, as well as playing ultimate frisbee and soccer.
alau@longviewassets.com
Connect on LinkedIn














 

CLOSE X

R.B. (Biff) Matthews
Chairman of Longview
Member, Investment Committee


In addition to participating actively in the firm’s investment decisions, as a member of Longview’s Investment Committee, Biff, along with Doug and Emily, enjoys interacting with Longview’s clients.
Biff is a graduate of the University of Toronto and Oxford University, and has studied and written about what works in investing for more than 20 years.
After practising law in Toronto, most recently as a partner of McCarthy Tetrault, Biff acted as President of Manitou Investment Management for 13 years before starting Longview.
Biff is a past Chairman of World Wildlife Fund Canada and Outward Bound Ontario. He serves on the Board of E-L Financial Corporation.
When not working, Biff enjoys reading widely, travel, golf and spending time in the country with his wife, Sue, and their adult children.
bmatthews@longviewassets.com
Connect on LinkedIn














 

CLOSE X

Doug McCutcheon
President of Longview
Chairman, Investment Committee


Doug chairs Longview’s Investment Committee, which is responsible for all of the firm’s investment decisions. In addition, along with Biff and Emily, Doug enjoys interacting with Longview’s clients.
Doug has been an investor in public and private companies around the world for more than 30 years.
Prior to joining Longview, Doug was an investment banker for 25 years, primarily based in London, England. Most recently, Doug was Managing Director and Head of Healthcare Investment Banking in Europe, the Middle East and Asia at UBS, having started his career at S.G. Warburg & Co. Ltd., a predecessor firm of UBS.
Doug is a graduate of Queen’s University (Bachelor of Commerce). He currently serves on the Boards of The Sterling Hall School (Chairman) and Worldwide Healthcare Trust PLC.
In addition to investing, Doug enjoys spending time with his wife, Deborah, and their three children, as well as participating in various sports and the arts.  His philanthropic passions are healthcare and education.
dmccutcheon@longviewassets.com
Connect on LinkedIn














 

CLOSE X

Emily Won, CFA, CPA, CA
Partner
Member, Investment Committee


As a member of Longview’s Investment Committee, Emily shares responsibility for the firm’s investment decisions. In addition, along with Biff and Doug, she enjoys interacting with Longview’s clients.
Prior to joining Longview, Emily was an Executive Director in Institutional Equity Sales at CIBC World Markets and Merrill Lynch.  Before that, she worked in Equity Research at Merrill Lynch and TD Securities.
Emily earned her bachelor of business administration from the Schulich School of Business as well as her Chartered Accountancy (CA, CPA) designation with Arthur Andersen. She is also a CFA® charterholder.
Emily is a member of the CFA Society Toronto and previously served on the CFA Society Toronto Equity Committee and the National Ballet School Foundation Board.  She is a past executive member of the Havergal College Parents Association.
When not being kept busy by their two young daughters, Emily and her husband, Andrew, enjoy discovering new restaurants and travelling.
ewon@longviewassets.com













